If I may suggest an improvement:<p><pre><code>  function isPrime(n) {
    var re = /^1?$|^(11+?)\1+$/,
          s = (new Array(n+1)).join(&#x27;1&#x27;);

    return !re.test(s);
  }</code></pre>

nice trick!<p>here a JS implementation<p><pre><code>    function isPrime(n) {
      var re = /^1?$|^(11+?)\1+$/;
      var s = [];
      while (n -- > 0)
        s.push(1);
      return !re.test(s.join(&#x27;&#x27;));
    }</code></pre>
